## 📺 Alien TV Presenter

One of the most complex visual elements — a fully animated alien news reader drawn entirely with pygame shapes (no images).

### `draw_alien_reader(surface, rx, ry, blink_t)`

| Feature | How it works |
|---|---|
| Wobbly tentacles | `math.sin(blink_t * 0.08)` offsets each tentacle up/down |
| Swaying antennas | `math.sin(blink_t * 0.06)` sways left/right |
| Blinking eyes | Every 55 frames: draws closed eyelid lines instead of eye circles |
| Eye look | `math.sin(blink_t * 0.03)` shifts pupils slightly left/right |
| Mouth | Alternates open/closed every 10 frames (`blink_t // 10 % 2`) |
| Floating speech bubble | `math.sin(blink_t * 0.15)` gently bobs it up/down |

### Speech Bubble
Cycles through 12 alien news lines every 110 frames:
```python
spoken = spoken_lines[(blink_timer // 110) % len(spoken_lines)]
```
Lines include: *"DOOMED!!"*, *"NOT A DRILL"*, *"I QUIT."* etc.

### News Ticker
Scrolls 10 alien headlines across the bottom of the TV screen:
```python
ticker_x -= ticker_speed        # move left each frame
if ticker_x <= -ticker_total_w:
    ticker_x = 0.0              # seamless loop

canvas.set_clip(ticker_bar_rect)   # clips text inside TV bounds
canvas.blit(ticker_surf, ...)
canvas.set_clip(None)
```
Two copies of the ticker are blitted side by side so it never shows a gap.

